pr_title: Add component to fetch list of journals
pr_body:
This PR adds a component to fetch the list of journals from the database. 
I have used a JSON server as a fake REST API to be later replaced by the graphQL resources. 
To run the server locally, use: 
`npx json-server --watch data/db.json --port 8000`

We can probably add a searchbar later to search for a particular journal.

Commands to reflect the current changes:
Pull the latest changes.
If you do not have yarn installed on your local, use : `npm i -g yarn`
Enter `yarn` in root directory. 
To start the project, use: `yarn start`.
Please make sure you don't have the package-lock.json. If you do, please delete it after the yarn install.
cc: @yochannah @ikayz @d-e-v-esh
